SARS-CoV-2-specific T cell receptors after disease and vaccination

Maria S. Benitez-Cantos

03/09/2021

1 Introduction

This notebook contains the code for the generation of most of the plots of my masters thesis titled "SARS-CoV-2-specific T cell receptors after disease and vaccination". More code and information regarding the generation of the used datasets is available upon request.

2.1 Metadata

Two sample metadata files are necessary:

  • repertoire_metadata: contains sample IDs and their respective groups
repertoire_metadata <- readRDS("data/repertoire_metadata.rds")
  • adaptive_metadata: contains sample metadata provided by Adaptive Biotechnologies:
adaptive_metadata <- readRDS("data/adaptive_metadata.rds")

2.2 Data

  • breadth_depth: contains spike and non-spike breadth and depth measurements:
breadth_depth <- readRDS("data/breadth_depth.rds")
  • metaclono_annotation: contains information of all the SARS-CoV-2-specific TCRs found in the samples:
metaclono_annotation <- readRDS("data/metaclono_annotation.rds")
  • covid_networks: a list of igraph objects that contain all the SARS-CoV-2-specific TCR networks:
covid_networks <- readRDS("data/covid_networks.rds")
  • covid_global_metrics: global network metrics for every SARS-CoV-2-specific TCR network:
covid_global_metrics <- readRDS("data/covid_global_metrics.rds")
  • covid_sns_local_metrics: local network metrics of SARS-CoV-2-specific nodes (TCRs):
covid_sns_local_metrics <- readRDS("data/covid_sns_local_metrics.rds")

3 Results

3.1 Preliminary TCR repertoire analysis

3.1.1 Fig. 3a: T cell fraction

my_comparisons <- list( c("Convalescent", "Vaccinated"), c("Vaccinated", "Placebo"), c("Convalescent", "Placebo") )

lymphopenia <- adaptive_metadata %>%
  mutate(Group = factor(case_when(grepl("Placebo", sample_tags) ~ "Placebo",
                           grepl("vaccine", sample_tags) ~ "Vaccinated",
                           grepl("Convalescent", sample_tags) ~ "Convalescent",
                           TRUE ~ "Convalescent"),
         levels = c("Convalescent", "Vaccinated", "Placebo"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Group, y = fraction_productive_of_cells, color = Group)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_x_discrete(name = NULL) +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Fraction of T-cells in PBMC") +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
  stat_compare_means(comparisons = my_comparisons, label = "p.signif", method = "wilcox.test", size = 3.2) +
  theme_pubr() +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10),
        legend.position = "none")

3.2.3 Fig. 5a: TCR hits lollipop plot

mean_pos <- function(a, b){
  a + ((b-a)/2)
}


hits.data <- metaclono_annotation %>%
  left_join(adaptive_metadata, by = c("Sample" = "sample_name")) %>%
  group_by(Sample, protein_coordinate) %>%
  summarise(breadth = n() / productive_rearrangements,
            depth = sum(templates) / productive_templates) %>%
  left_join(repertoire_metadata) %>%
  group_by(Group, protein_coordinate) %>%
  summarise(avg_breadth = mean(breadth),
            avg_depth = mean(depth)) %>%
  separate(protein_coordinate, into = c("prot", "coords"), sep = " ") %>%
  separate(coords, into = c("epitope_sindex", "epitope_eindex"), sep = ":") %>%
  mutate(epitope_sindex = as.numeric(epitope_sindex),
         epitope_eindex = as.numeric(epitope_eindex)) %>%
  mutate(epitope_size = epitope_eindex - epitope_sindex) %>%
  mutate(epitope_mean = (epitope_size / 2) + epitope_sindex) %>%
  filter(epitope_size <= 1000) %>% # Remove one long epitope (inespecific) 
  mutate(Group = factor(Group, levels = rev(c("Convalescent", "Vaccinated", "Placebo")))) %>%
  mutate(Group = case_when(
    Group == "Placebo" ~ 1,
    Group == "Vaccinated" ~ 2,
    Group == "Convalescent" ~ 3,
  ))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'Sample', 'protein_coordinate' (override with `.groups` argument)
## Joining, by = "Sample"
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'Group' (override with `.groups` argument)
covid_coords <- data.frame(start = c(266, 21555, 25384, 26220, 26472, 27191, 27387, 27759, 27887, 28259, 29533),
                           end = c(21555, 25384, 26220, 26472, 27191, 27387, 27759, 27887, 28259, 29533, 29674),
                           gene = c("ORF1ab", "S", "ORF3a", "E", "M", "ORF6", "ORF7a", "ORF7b", "ORF8", "N", "ORF10"),
                           y = c(rep(0.55, 11))) %>% 
  mutate(gene = factor(gene, levels = c("ORF1ab", "S", "ORF3a", "E", "M", "ORF6", "ORF7a", "ORF7b", "ORF8", "N", "ORF10")))

Plot:

lollipop <- ggplot() +
geom_segment(data = hits.data, aes(x=epitope_mean, xend=epitope_mean, y=0.5, yend=Group), alpha = 0.1) +
geom_point(data = hits.data, aes(x=epitope_mean, y = Group, size = log10(avg_breadth), color = log10(avg_depth)), alpha=0.6) +
geom_gene_arrow(data = covid_coords, mapping = aes(xmin = start, xmax = end, fill = gene, y = y),
  arrowhead_height = unit(5, "mm"), arrowhead_width = unit(1, "mm"), arrow_body_height = unit(5, "mm"), 
  linetype = c("dotted", "solid", "dotted", "solid", "solid", "dotted", "dotted", "dotted", "dotted", "solid", "dotted"), 
  size = c(0.2,0.5,0.2,0.5,0.5,0.2,0.2,0.2,0.2,0.5,0.2)) + # 
  annotate(geom="text", x=23400, y=0.555, label="Spike", size = 3) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 1.5) +

scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set3", name = "Gene") +
scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0), limits = c(0, 30000), breaks = c(5000, 10000, 15000, 20000, 25000), name = "SARS-CoV-2 genomic coordinate") +
scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(1,2,3), labels = c("Placebo", "Vaccinated", "Convalescent"), expand = c(.1,.1)) +
